# Dineros.cc — Predictive budgeting & financial management

Dineros.cc is a Nuxt 4 + TypeScript application that provides predictive budgeting, real-time spending optimization, and simplified accounting. It ships a full-stack monorepo with a Nuxt app (frontend + Nitro/H3 API) and a companion microservice. Core domains include accounts/registers, recurring entries, reconciliation, budgets/categories, savings goals, reporting, and integrations (Plaid, crypto via Alchemy).

- Source-available, custom non-commercial license (see LICENSE)
- Database: MySQL 8 via Prisma ORM
- Caching/queues: Redis + BullMQ
- Integrations: Plaid, Postmark, OpenAI, Alchemy (EVM chains)
- Infra: Dockerfiles, GitHub Actions CI/CD, Kubernetes manifests for GKE

See README.md for quickstart and AGENTS.md for AI-agent specific environment notes (e.g., Cursor Cloud DB override).

## Tech stack (from repository evidence)

- Frontend: Nuxt 4, Vue 3, Tailwind CSS, Pinia (@pinia/nuxt), @nuxt/ui, @nuxt/icon, @nuxt/fonts
- Backend API: Nitro/H3 under app/server/api/* (file-based routes)
- Language/tooling: TypeScript, ESLint, Vitest, Playwright
- Data: Prisma ORM (app/prisma/schema.prisma), MySQL 8, prisma-field-encryption
- Runtime infra: Redis, BullMQ for background jobs; nuxt-cron for cron tasks
- Integrations: Plaid, Postmark, OpenAI, Google Cloud logging/storage (dev deps), NATS client present
- Security: TOTP, WebAuthn Passkeys, JWT, RSA (rotateable); rate limiting with Redis
- CI/CD: GitHub Actions (PR checks, CodeQL, Sonar optionally), image build and push to gcr.io, deploy to GKE using templated manifests

## Audience

- Primary: Project maintainers and contributors
- Secondary: AI agents and CI automation (Cursor-style). Follow .cursor/rules/* and AGENTS.md when running in cloud agents.

## Monorepo layout (top-level)

- app/: Nuxt app (UI + API), Prisma schema/migrations, services, queues, cron, tests
- microservice/: companion service with its own Prisma client and routes
- .deploy/: Kubernetes templates (envsubst-based)
- .github/: Actions workflows and composite actions
- scripts/: Ops/dev scripts (DB restore, Prisma governance checks, key rotation helpers)
- docs/: focused docs (e.g., post-restore encryption plan)
